rounds.response:
I’m in the Big Blind (out of position) with 4♥ Q♣, facing a 20-chip bet from P1 who already put in 10 as the Small Blind. The pot is 30, and I must decide whether to call, fold, or raise (I’m allowed to check only if the bet were 0).

Q4o is an offsuit, non-paired, low-connected hand. Equity vs a typical Button open range (≈70 %) is only ~35-40 % and drops heavily out of position. My required equity to call is 20/(30+20)=40 % if we assume no further action; however, OOP with a weak kicker it will be hard to realize that equity, so raw equity overstates profitability.

Folding is neutral (loses 10 chips already posted). Raising here would build a bigger pot OOP with a mediocre holding that rarely flops well. The most economical line is to fold now and avoid further bleeding of chips.

[Fold]
